      "source": [
        "# Ideal Gas Law Professional Calculator (PV = nRT)\n",
        "\n",
        "## Aim\n",
        "To compute any unknown variable in the Ideal Gas Law equation.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Equation\n",
        "PV = nRT\n",
        "\n",
        "This notebook can calculate:\n",
        "- Pressure (P)\n",
        "- Volume (V)\n",
        "- Number of moles (n)\n",
        "- Temperature (T)\n",
        "\n",
        "Given the other three variables."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "vJH9CH2YfFfR"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "\n",
        "# Ideal Gas Law Calculator (No input version - works on phone)\n",
        "\n",
        "R = 0.0821\n",
        "\n",
        "# ====== CHANGE THESE VALUES ONLY ======\n",
        "P = 1        # Pressure in atm\n",
        "V = 22.4     # Volume in Liters\n",
        "T = 273      # Temperature in Kelvin\n",
        "# ======================================\n",
        "\n",
        "n = (P * V) / (R * T)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Given:\")\n",
        "print(\"Pressure =\", P, \"atm\")\n",
        "print(\"Volume =\", V, \"L\")\n",
        "print(\"Temperature =\", T, \"K\")\n",
        "print(\"---------------------------\")\n",
        "print(\"Number of moles (n) =\", n)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "OPVIRecqiCtR",
        "outputId": "292bc3ed-9e78-40bb-a0fc-2a6cafe74f3b"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Given:\n",
            "Pressure = 1 atm\n",
            "Volume = 22.4 L\n",
            "Temperature = 273 K\n",
            "---------------------------\n",
            "Number of moles (n) = 0.9994066023298664\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "V = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]\n",
        "P = [5, 4, 3, 2, 1]\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.plot(V, P)\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"Volume (L)\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"Pressure (atm)\")\n",
        "plt.title(\"Boyle's Law: Pressure vs Volume\")\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
